item.title: Structured Big Data Analysis
item.description: I completed the Programming for Data Science with Python nanodegree at Udacity. The program was outstanding. It was formatted in a way that I really like to learn: a short video lesson, a short text recap/expansion of the content, and then a portion to practice what you learned. This course had three main technical objectives and two capstone projects. Focus 1: SQL, Beginner to Advanced The first objective was to learn SQL.
